Eskom has announced that load shedding will be reduced from Stage 4 to Stage 3 over the weekend. In a statement on Friday, the power utility said Stage 1 load shedding is expected on Sunday morning. “Stage 4 load shedding will continue to be implemented until 05:00 tomorrow. Thereafter, Stage 3 load shedding will be implemented from Saturday 05:00 until 05:00 on Sunday. “Stage 1 load shedding will then be implemented until 16:00 on Sunday and then revert to Stage 3 load shedding.” Eskom said further updates will be published as soon as any significant changes occur. – SAnews.gov.za